WEBVTT

00:01.169 --> 00:03.771
You know the kind of guy
who does nothing
but bad things...

00:03.804 --> 00:06.707
and then wonders why
his life sucks?

00:06.740 --> 00:11.145
Well, that was me.
Every time somethin' good
happened to me,

00:11.179 --> 00:13.281
somethin' bad
was always waitin'
around the corner.

00:15.516 --> 00:17.085
Karma.

00:17.118 --> 00:19.220
That's when I realized
I had to change.

00:20.754 --> 00:23.391
So I made a list
of everything bad
I've ever done,

00:23.424 --> 00:26.394
and, one by one,
I'm gonna make up
for all my mistakes.

00:26.427 --> 00:28.362
I'm just tryin'
to be a better person.

00:28.396 --> 00:32.233
My name is Earl.

00:32.266 --> 00:35.336
[ Earl Narrating ] Joy and
Darnell had recently learned
a few tips on how to fight...

00:35.369 --> 00:37.471
while watchin' Dr. Phil
on TV.

00:37.505 --> 00:42.576
You are making me feel
very angry because my needs
aren't bein' met.

00:42.610 --> 00:47.248
And you are making me feel
angry because your needs
don't make sense.

00:47.281 --> 00:50.118
[ Earl Narrating ]
Unfortunately, one episode
of Dr. Phil...

00:50.151 --> 00:52.720
couldn't undo years of
watchin' Springer.

00:52.753 --> 00:55.623
Don't be a dummy, damn it!
Just do what I tell you to!

00:55.656 --> 00:59.093
Throw me a surprise party
for my birthday next month.
But you won't be surprised.

00:59.127 --> 01:02.296
I can act surprised.
Look.

01:02.330 --> 01:05.533
[ Earl Narrating ]
Not only was the two of them
arguing fun to watch,

01:05.566 --> 01:08.369
but it also gave me a chance
to do number 183 on my list--

01:08.402 --> 01:11.439
never took Joy's side.

01:11.472 --> 01:13.641
When we were married,
I wasn't very good...

01:13.674 --> 01:15.609
at backing up my wife
in arguments with strangers.

01:15.643 --> 01:17.578
Twelve ball, side pocket.

01:20.314 --> 01:23.817
Okay, do it again,
and I'm gonna pop those booby
implants of yours...

01:23.851 --> 01:26.520
and make you fly around this bar
like a loose balloon.

01:26.554 --> 01:29.157
It was an accident, Joy.

01:29.190 --> 01:31.425
And I think they're real.

01:31.459 --> 01:34.228
Oh, so you're on her side?

01:34.262 --> 01:37.631
[ Narrating ] And I definitely
didn't take her side when it
came to arguments with family.

01:40.368 --> 01:43.204
Oh, I know you did not
just monkey-grab a chip
out of that bowl.

01:43.237 --> 01:47.575
That actually takes quite
a bit of skill, Joy.
Try to dip one in the salsa.

01:47.608 --> 01:50.378
Oh, so you're on his side?

01:50.411 --> 01:52.646
[ Earl Narrating ]
I didn't even take her side
in arguments with things...

01:52.680 --> 01:54.682
that couldn't argue back.

01:54.715 --> 01:56.784
Dang it!
Got crab juice in my eye.

01:56.817 --> 01:59.453
That's 'cause you cracked it
the wrong way. You should
always crack away from you.

01:59.487 --> 02:01.789
Oh, so you're on
the crab's side now?

02:01.822 --> 02:04.325
[ Earl Narrating ]
I was. And it was time
to make up for it.

02:04.358 --> 02:06.727
I've been waitin' my whole life
for somebody to throw me
a surprise party.

02:06.760 --> 02:09.597
I'm sick of waitin'.
This year I want one.

02:09.630 --> 02:12.333
She's got a good point,
Darnell.
You hear that?

02:12.366 --> 02:14.335
And that's comin' from
the husband I left.

02:14.368 --> 02:16.870
You can only imagine what kind
of thin ice you're on.

02:16.904 --> 02:19.340
Fine. I'll throw you
a surprise party
for your birthday.

02:19.373 --> 02:23.211
[ Cell Phone Rings ]
Gotta take that.

02:23.244 --> 02:26.814
It's about damn time
you called me back.
I am in a bind here.

02:26.847 --> 02:29.683
[ Earl Narrating ]
The bind she was talkin'
about was complicated.

02:29.717 --> 02:32.186
It started 'cause Joy was
obsessed with some TV show...

02:32.220 --> 02:34.388
called
Britney and Kevin: Chaotic.

02:34.422 --> 02:37.291
I swear, those two are
like American royalty.

02:37.325 --> 02:39.460
Oh, snap!

02:39.493 --> 02:42.596
Look at that big-ass
TV disappear into that
entertainment center.

02:42.630 --> 02:44.932
I want a disappearin' TV.
Yeah.

02:44.965 --> 02:49.537
With a bottle of Cristal
sittin' on top.
That's how the Federlines roll.

02:49.570 --> 02:54.708
We're gonna get us one of those
disappearin' TV furniture
things. I mean it. I want it.

02:54.742 --> 02:57.611
[ Earl Narrating ]
So about a week ago, Joy
finally saved up enough money...

02:57.645 --> 02:59.813
to get that disappearin' TV.

02:59.847 --> 03:02.650
But unfortunately,
she ran into a big problem.

03:02.683 --> 03:05.353
[ Grunting ]

03:06.820 --> 03:08.822
I got an idea.

03:08.856 --> 03:11.659
Come on. You got it.
Push.

03:11.692 --> 03:13.561
Come on.
It's almost in there.

03:13.594 --> 03:15.896
Push.

03:15.929 --> 03:18.699
I got an idea.

03:18.732 --> 03:21.669
Damn it! How did
Britney and Kevin do it?

03:21.702 --> 03:24.438
[ Grunting ]

03:26.774 --> 03:29.543
[ Earl Narrating ]
When Joy went to return it, she
ran into yet another problem.

03:29.577 --> 03:31.845
- You can't return this.
- What?

03:31.879 --> 03:34.648
- The receipt has gum in it.
- I know. It's Fruit Stripe.
Just pull it off.

03:34.682 --> 03:37.285
I'm sure you can still see
the disappearin' TV furniture
thing on there.

03:37.318 --> 03:39.553
The gum took off half
the item number.

03:39.587 --> 03:42.423
Sorry. The system
won't take it back
without an item number.

03:42.456 --> 03:45.526
What? Uh-uh.
Oh, hell, no.

03:45.559 --> 03:48.562
[ Earl Narrating ]
After 45 minutes of arguin'
and throwin' a shoe,

03:48.596 --> 03:52.866
Joy realized she was
just gonna have to make
the best of her situation.

03:55.035 --> 03:58.038
[ TV Turns On ]

03:58.071 --> 04:01.742
So much glare out here, I can't
tell if that's the white lady
judge or the black lady judge.

04:05.979 --> 04:09.583
Hey, get out of
my damn livin' room!
[ Thunderclap ]

04:09.617 --> 04:13.321
Oh, God, please, no.

04:13.354 --> 04:18.626
I need a third umbrella!
Maybe we should unplug
the cord before--

04:18.659 --> 04:21.762
Son of a bitch.

04:24.632 --> 04:28.302
Okay, I'm leavin' it here.
It's yours.
I have returned it.

04:28.336 --> 04:30.571
And somehow or another,
I'm gonna get
my $3,000 back.

04:30.604 --> 04:32.306
- No, you won't.
- Yes, I will.

04:32.340 --> 04:35.876
- No. You won't.
- Yes, I will.

04:35.909 --> 04:37.878
** [ Rock ]

04:44.652 --> 04:46.487
[ Man ]
* Ooh-hoo

04:50.491 --> 04:55.496
* Billy Joe shot a man
while robbin' his castle *

04:55.529 --> 04:57.565
Cha-ching!

04:57.598 --> 04:59.833
* Ooh-hoo

04:59.867 --> 05:04.438
* Go on
Take the money and run *

05:04.472 --> 05:08.108
* Go on
Take the money and run *

05:08.141 --> 05:10.544
* Ooh-hoo

05:10.578 --> 05:13.581
I got my $3,000!
[ Laughing ]

05:15.115 --> 05:17.885
* Go on
Take the money and run *

05:17.918 --> 05:21.855
[ Earl Narrating ]
Joy stashed the truck
in the woods until today,

05:21.889 --> 05:24.958
when she finally got a call
from the one guy in Camden
County who would buy anything.

05:24.992 --> 05:27.895
- It's too risky.
- Too risky?

05:27.928 --> 05:30.431
You sold a damn
Iranian baby.

05:30.464 --> 05:34.502
Yeah, but it didn't have
"Iranian Baby" painted on
the side of it in big letters.

05:34.535 --> 05:36.937
Like they're not
gonna know he's Iranian
once he's old enough to talk.

05:36.970 --> 05:41.041
Look, this is a great deal.
All I want is the $3,000
that they owe me.

05:41.074 --> 05:43.777
Whatever.
I don't buy stolen trucks
from amateurs.

05:43.811 --> 05:46.580
- Why not?
- Same reason I don't let
amateurs cut my hair.

05:46.614 --> 05:48.582
They make mistakes.

05:48.616 --> 05:51.385
It was not mistake.

05:51.419 --> 05:53.086
Yeah, well, you better pray
I find that earlobe.

05:56.457 --> 05:58.559
He won't find.

05:58.592 --> 06:01.595
Jasper is too much sissy
to be real criminal.

06:01.629 --> 06:05.399
This is why we live
in cement closet.
Bring me to this truck.

06:05.433 --> 06:08.536
I will buy with my own money
I steal from Jasper.

06:08.569 --> 06:10.638
I like you.
If I could ever get used...

06:10.671 --> 06:13.841
to staring at that thing on
your face, we could hang out.

06:16.176 --> 06:19.647
This is no truck.
This is giant camper.

06:19.680 --> 06:22.583
Something is fishes.
You are police.
I know it.

06:22.616 --> 06:25.052
Oh, calm down.
I just gotta pick up
the truck keys.

06:25.085 --> 06:28.756
So jumpy
all of a sudden.
I just don't like surprises.

06:30.458 --> 06:32.760
[ All ]
Surprise!

06:34.728 --> 06:37.931
[ Panting ]

06:37.965 --> 06:41.569
- What the hell are you doing?
- Throwing you a surprise
birthday party.

06:41.602 --> 06:44.472
- My birthday is not
until next month.
- That's the surprise part.

06:44.505 --> 06:46.707
- Idiot.
- It was Earl's idea.

06:46.740 --> 06:48.509
Y'all are all idiots!

06:55.916 --> 06:58.418
I think you should go
talk to her.
Dumb dummies!

07:00.588 --> 07:02.089
Yeah,
that's not gonna happen.

07:06.159 --> 07:08.896
That lady dropped her purse,
and some stuff rolled out.

07:11.832 --> 07:13.634
Cool.
It's an earlobe.

07:15.102 --> 07:17.471
So you planned all this
because of some list thing?

07:17.505 --> 07:20.741
Number 183--
never took Joy's side.
Now, come back in.

07:20.774 --> 07:23.611
We got a whole piÃ±ata full of
cigarettes for you to swing at.

07:23.644 --> 07:26.213
- I don't feel like it.
- Why? You're the one
that wanted a party.

07:26.246 --> 07:28.716
Not when it's
gonna cost me $3,000.

07:38.258 --> 07:41.161
[ Balloon Squeaking ]

07:44.665 --> 07:47.868
[ High-pitched ]
* We represent
the Lollipop Guild *

07:47.901 --> 07:50.938
* The Lollipop Guild
The Lollipop Guild *

07:50.971 --> 07:54.274
Randy, those aren't
helium balloons.

07:54.307 --> 07:56.810
[ Normal Voice ]
Oh, too bad.
[ Balloon Squeaking ]

08:02.049 --> 08:05.252
- You stole a truck?
- Because they wouldn't
give me my money back.

08:05.285 --> 08:08.121
It was a crime of principle,
like when Rosa Parks
stole that bus.

08:08.155 --> 08:10.624
- They wouldn't even
give you store credit?
- No.

08:10.658 --> 08:13.827
- That doesn't seem fair.
- Thank you.

08:13.861 --> 08:16.129
Which is why you have to
help me sell the truck.

08:16.163 --> 08:18.899
Sell the truck?
Joy, that's against the law.

08:18.932 --> 08:21.268
Earl, this is not about the law.
It's about right and wrong.

08:21.301 --> 08:24.738
Isn't that what your list
is about? Rightin' wrongs?
Do unto others?

08:24.772 --> 08:27.074
All that Robin Hood,
Batman, Jesus stuff?

08:27.107 --> 08:30.711
Well, you got a good point.
The store did do you wrong.

08:30.744 --> 08:35.649
I don't know if Jesus or Batman
would sell the truck,
but Robin Hood might.

08:35.683 --> 08:38.652
Okay, I'll do it.

08:38.686 --> 08:41.188
But you're not gettin'
a penny more than $3,000.

08:41.221 --> 08:43.624
Of course not.
That would be wrong.

08:43.657 --> 08:46.159
[ Earl Narrating ]
The first thing you have to do
with a stolen truck...

08:46.193 --> 08:49.096
is make sure it can't
get traced back to its owner.

08:49.129 --> 08:51.799
Randy was especially excited
about this.

08:51.832 --> 08:54.334
Somethin' about the combination
of fumes and bright colors...

08:54.367 --> 08:57.838
made Randy love to spray paint.

08:57.871 --> 09:00.107
In fact, he made
a name for himself...

09:00.140 --> 09:03.243
as one of Camden County's
most gifted graffiti artists.

09:06.179 --> 09:08.716
It's perfect, Earl.
Yeah, it really is.

09:08.749 --> 09:10.818
I just don't know
if it's a good idea...

09:10.851 --> 09:13.086
to paint your name in
six-foot letters on the side
of a stolen truck.

09:15.823 --> 09:18.325
I'm gonna go into town and
get some more white paint
to cover up my name.

09:18.358 --> 09:20.861
Good idea.

09:20.894 --> 09:23.631
If the cops come while I'm gone,
tip it on its side.

09:27.901 --> 09:31.839
That's pretty. I'd probably
read more often if people
wrote like that all the time.

09:31.872 --> 09:34.041
What's in there, anyway?
I don't know.

09:34.074 --> 09:36.810
You haven't even looked yet?
No.

09:36.844 --> 09:39.246
I just want my three grand.
I don't really care
what's back there.

09:39.279 --> 09:41.214
But there could be
$3,000 worth of stuff in here--

09:41.248 --> 09:43.784
TVs, stereos, nunchakus.

09:43.817 --> 09:47.054
Be a lot easier to sell that
stuff than this stolen truck.

09:49.857 --> 09:52.392
Oh.

09:52.425 --> 09:55.162
Wait!

09:55.195 --> 09:58.265
[ Man ]
Ow!

09:58.298 --> 10:00.801
[ Screams ]

10:04.004 --> 10:06.640
There's a man in there, Joy!
There's a man in the truck.

10:06.674 --> 10:09.242
I know.
A hairy one.

10:14.848 --> 10:18.018
Why is there a man
in the truck, Joy?
I don't know!

10:18.051 --> 10:19.953
Maybe he was in there
when you stole it.

10:19.987 --> 10:23.056
Do I look stupid enough
to steal a truck with a man
in the back of it?

10:23.090 --> 10:25.192
[ Earl Narrating ]
Turns out Joy was that stupid.

10:25.225 --> 10:30.363
Some poor guy was unloadin'
boxes when Joy decided to
get her revenge on the store.

10:30.397 --> 10:32.733
After she ran off,
he tried to get out,
but the door was locked.

10:34.001 --> 10:37.270
Okay, you got me.

10:37.304 --> 10:40.908
Let's get back to work now.
Eric!

10:40.941 --> 10:47.214
Help!

10:47.247 --> 10:51.118
[ Earl Narrating ] Luckily,
this truck was from a store that
sold a little bit of everything.

10:51.151 --> 10:55.255
So he had plenty to eat and
plenty to keep him entertained.

10:59.793 --> 11:02.863
Yes! Nice.

11:11.071 --> 11:13.707
Help! Anybody?
Oh, my God.
Oh, my God.

11:13.741 --> 11:17.377
Why did I help you?
Why? Why? Why?

11:17.410 --> 11:20.313
All right, all right. Look.
We'll leave him in
the back of the truck.

11:20.347 --> 11:23.216
We'll make an anonymous call
so they know where to find him.

11:23.250 --> 11:26.053
I am not leavin' this truck.
I still need to sell it.

11:26.086 --> 11:28.822
With a man locked in the back?
Don't you think that's
gonna be problem?

11:28.856 --> 11:31.859
- For the person who buys it.
- We're not sellin' a truck
with a man in the back!

11:31.892 --> 11:34.194
Look, if we let him out, he's
gonna see what we look like.

11:35.528 --> 11:37.931
Maybe not.

11:37.965 --> 11:40.801
[ Earl Narrating ]
We finally figured out a way
to release the guy Joy stole.

11:40.834 --> 11:42.970
We just had to
stay out of sight.

11:43.003 --> 11:45.238
[ British Accent ]
All right, love, I want you
to listen to me carefully...

11:45.272 --> 11:47.808
and do everything I say,
and everything'll be okay.

11:47.841 --> 11:51.111
Why are you talking funny?
'Cause I don't want him
to identify my voice.

11:51.144 --> 11:54.281
Yeah, but it sounds weird.
It's British.
That's how they sound.

11:54.314 --> 11:57.150
British people don't steal
trucks. They drink tea
and live in castles.

11:57.184 --> 12:00.320
You still out there?
[ British Accent ]
Uh, I-- I'm here, ma'am.

12:00.353 --> 12:02.956
Uh, here's what
I want you to do.

12:02.990 --> 12:05.793
I want you to take off
your shirt and use it
as a blindfold.

12:05.826 --> 12:07.928
You sound like a gay
Kermit the Frog.

12:07.961 --> 12:10.898
Okay! Blindfold's on!

12:10.931 --> 12:14.134
Right, then.
Now, when the back door opens,
I want you to start running,

12:14.167 --> 12:16.269
and don't look back
or I'll shoot you.

12:16.303 --> 12:21.241
And by the way,
what you call soccer,
we call football.

12:26.046 --> 12:28.215
See?
This worked out okay.

12:29.516 --> 12:31.484
[ Grunts ]

12:34.587 --> 12:39.526
Crap, crap, crap! Why me?
Why do bad things always happen
to good people?

12:39.559 --> 12:42.796
Seems like most of the
bad things are happening
to this guy.

12:42.830 --> 12:45.498
Let's just get out of here
before he wakes up.
We can't go, Joy.

12:45.532 --> 12:47.835
What if a wild animal comes
along and mauls him
while he's out?

12:47.868 --> 12:50.003
Just pee a circle around him.
That'll keep the animals away.

12:50.037 --> 12:53.173
I'm not gonna pee a circle
around him. What if
he wakes up and sees me?

12:53.206 --> 12:56.409
So I gotta do everything?
Look, we're not leavin' him.

12:56.443 --> 12:58.812
Help me get him
in the back of the truck.
We gotta get him to a hospital.

12:58.846 --> 13:01.414
We'll get caught.
No, we won't.

13:01.448 --> 13:06.019
We'll drop him off and
drive away like people do
with babies and grandparents.

13:08.388 --> 13:13.226
So me and Joy put the passed-out
guy in the back of the truck
and headed to the hospital.

13:18.365 --> 13:20.868
You like my earrings?

13:20.901 --> 13:23.536
Yeah, I do like those earrings.
I was about to say
something earlier,

13:23.570 --> 13:26.239
but then I got distracted
by the hostage and all.

13:26.273 --> 13:30.243
Where'd you get 'em?
Flea market. You know the guy
who sells the tube socks?

13:30.277 --> 13:34.147
The guy with the regular
tube socks or the guy
with the irregular tube socks?

13:34.181 --> 13:37.084
Irregular. Guy with regular
went out of business.
Good. He was a jerk.

13:37.117 --> 13:39.452
Thought his socks made
the world go around.

13:39.486 --> 13:42.355
Yeah. Anyway,
I got the earrings from
irregular tube sock's wife.

13:42.389 --> 13:44.391
- They're nice.
- Thanks.

13:44.424 --> 13:49.262
- One's bigger than the other.
- Yeah, I wasn't gonna
say anything.

13:49.296 --> 13:53.366
Look, Earl, I know this
hasn't been a great day,

13:53.400 --> 13:56.569
but I really appreciate you
helpin' me out.

13:56.603 --> 13:59.572
Who knows?
Maybe one day we'll look back
on this as an adventure.

14:00.941 --> 14:02.409
Yeah, maybe so.

14:02.442 --> 14:04.477
[ Engine Chugging ]

14:04.511 --> 14:06.546
Outta gas?

14:09.116 --> 14:11.051
Yep.

14:13.353 --> 14:18.191
The plan was for me to walk to
a gas station while Joy stayed
behind to guard the truck.

14:18.225 --> 14:20.327
Hey, bring me
somethin'.
What?

14:20.360 --> 14:22.362
I don't know.
Somethin' fun.

14:22.395 --> 14:25.265
Surprise me.
But with chocolate and peanuts.

14:25.298 --> 14:28.468
- Snickers?
- Damn it, Earl,
I said surprise me!

14:31.304 --> 14:33.640
[ Earl Narrating ]
So I headed off.

14:33.673 --> 14:36.143
** [ Rock ]

14:36.176 --> 14:41.481
[ Man ]
* I got to run
to keep from hiding *

14:41.514 --> 14:46.053
* And I'm bound
to keep on riding *

14:46.086 --> 14:48.055
[ Earl Narrating ]
It was four miles of walking,

14:48.088 --> 14:53.426
but I got the gas and
made it back to the truck.

14:53.460 --> 14:56.163
* But I'm not gonna
let 'em catch me, no *

14:56.196 --> 14:58.531
* Not gonna let 'em
catch the midnight rider *

14:58.565 --> 15:02.302
Hey, Earl.
How'd you know
where to find us?

15:02.335 --> 15:05.538
I went back to the woods
and the truck was gone, but
I found the note you left.

15:05.572 --> 15:07.975
I didn't leave a note.
I know, Earl.

15:08.008 --> 15:10.477
I was being sarcastic.
You should've left a note.

15:10.510 --> 15:13.446
You don't have to add it
to your list or anything,
but it would've been nice.

15:13.480 --> 15:16.083
I'm sorry, Randy.
Where's Joy?

15:16.116 --> 15:18.918
I don't know.
I figured she was with you.

15:20.020 --> 15:22.455
Come here! Come here!

15:27.694 --> 15:29.662
[ Grunts ]

15:29.696 --> 15:31.631
There she is.

15:41.308 --> 15:43.510
- What the hell happened?
- Well--

15:43.543 --> 15:46.013
Apparently Joy was too hungry
to wait for me to get back,

15:46.046 --> 15:48.982
and she remembered
seein' snacks in the truck.

15:49.016 --> 15:51.951
[ British Accent ]
Yoo-hoo.
You still knocked out?

15:53.586 --> 15:56.123
Jolly good, then.

16:22.149 --> 16:24.484
Son of a bitch
Ferris Bueller'd me.

16:29.789 --> 16:33.193
Hey, Earl, how come we got
a guy in his underpants?

16:33.226 --> 16:36.296
'Cause he was in the back
of the truck and was
accidentally kidnapped.

16:36.329 --> 16:38.431
You know how Mom used
to say,

16:38.465 --> 16:41.434
"Always wear clean underwears,
'cause you never know
what's gonna happen?"

16:41.468 --> 16:43.536
I bet she was talkin'
about stuff like this.

16:43.570 --> 16:47.374
Probably. Randy, can you
put him in the truck?

16:56.116 --> 16:58.385
What do you hate more,
flies or mosquitoes?

16:58.418 --> 17:02.289
Why?
Just making conversation.
Damn, never mind.

17:02.322 --> 17:04.791
Mosquitoes.

17:04.824 --> 17:07.127
Me too.

17:07.160 --> 17:09.696
You know, they say mosquitoes
in Africa kill people.

17:09.729 --> 17:12.099
Can you imagine the size
those things gotta be?

17:12.132 --> 17:14.201
- Pretty big.
- [ Engine Starts ]

17:18.138 --> 17:21.708
- Randy, where's the guy?
- I put him in the truck,
like you said.

17:21.741 --> 17:24.544
I meant the back
of the truck!

17:35.388 --> 17:38.191
Drive faster!
He's gettin' away.
This is great, Earl.

17:38.225 --> 17:40.193
You never drive this fast
when I ask you to.

17:40.227 --> 17:43.230
Hey, ask him if we can have
bubble gum for dinner.

17:43.263 --> 17:45.465
Would you just hurry up?
We gotta catch him.
Relax.

17:45.498 --> 17:48.335
He'll run out of gas
sooner or later--

17:48.368 --> 17:51.271
Wait a minute. What are
we gonna do when we catch him?
He saw our face.

17:51.304 --> 17:53.806
- I think she has to kill him.
- She's not gonna
kill him, Randy.

17:53.840 --> 17:56.876
You're not gonna
kill him, are you?
No, I'm not gonna kill him!

17:56.909 --> 18:00.247
You could cut out his tongue.
He couldn't tell anyone what you
looked like with no tongue.

18:00.280 --> 18:02.549
Oh, wait, he could still
draw you. Unless you cut
off his fingers too.

18:02.582 --> 18:04.751
- Randy--
- Hey, at least he's thinkin'.

18:04.784 --> 18:07.287
- It's not his fault
he's bad at it.
- I got it.

18:07.320 --> 18:10.323
-You could stab him in the eyes.
-We're not stabbin' him
in the eyes.

18:10.357 --> 18:12.359
I just gotta make sure
he doesn't squeal on me.

18:12.392 --> 18:14.561
So we'll just snatch him up
and put him in a little cage
in the trailer.

18:14.594 --> 18:18.465
What?
Just until he becomes our
friend and promises not to tell.

18:18.498 --> 18:21.201
Joy, we're not puttin'
him in a cage.

18:21.234 --> 18:25.438
Well, what else should we do,
Negative Nancy? I don't hear
you givin' us any ideas.

18:25.472 --> 18:29.509
[ Earl Narrating ]
That's when I got the only
decent idea I had all day.

18:29.542 --> 18:33.613
This whole thing had gotten
so outta hand that there
was only one thing left to do.

18:35.948 --> 18:38.485
[ Joy ]
What are you doin'?
Are we outta gas?

18:38.518 --> 18:41.354
It's over, Joy.

18:41.388 --> 18:44.691
What do you mean, "it's over"?
It's not over.
What are you talkin' about?

18:44.724 --> 18:49.229
What are you doin'?
You said you were on my side!

18:49.262 --> 18:51.831
[ Earl Narrating ]
Joy didn't realize it,
but I was on her side.

18:51.864 --> 18:54.534
She asked me for my help
sellin' a stolen truck,

18:54.567 --> 18:58.238
but that turned into
a kidnapping and assault.

18:58.271 --> 19:01.508
And my past experience
as a criminal told me
it was time to call it off.

19:01.541 --> 19:03.843
Besides, my guess was that
the guy was so scared...

19:03.876 --> 19:06.513
he probably didn't even
get a good look at Joy.

19:06.546 --> 19:09.282
Unfortunately,
my guess was wrong.

19:09.316 --> 19:11.684
[ Camera Shutter Clicks ]
She was charged
with grand theft auto,

19:11.718 --> 19:13.753
kidnapping and assault.

19:13.786 --> 19:15.855
Which would've been
my second guess.

19:23.496 --> 19:26.633
Randy, do you think
it's my fault Joy went to jail?

19:28.868 --> 19:32.339
Randy?

19:32.372 --> 19:34.974
I'm tryin' to sleep, Earl.
Can't this wait till morning?

19:35.007 --> 19:39.346
You woke me up last night
to ask if I thought monkeys
ever worried about their looks.

19:39.379 --> 19:41.381
Oh, yeah. Sorry.

19:42.949 --> 19:45.285
Do you think they do?

19:45.318 --> 19:48.921
I already told you, if they
worried about their looks,
they'd wear pants.

19:48.955 --> 19:51.524
Yeah.

19:54.861 --> 19:57.697
Night, Randy.
Good night, Earl.
